text: - **iA Writer** ([https://ia.net/topics/category/writer]({{$url0}})): A Markdown syntax editor praised for its simplicity, though it lacks in note organization and related features.

- **Paper** ([https://papereditor.app/]({{$url0}})): A writing tool that offers an enhanced writing experience compared to iA Writer but has some bugs and limitations, making it suitable only for simple notes.
- **Obsidian** ([https://obsidian.md/]({{$url0}})): An application primarily used for organizing content, often paired with Vitepress to share notes online as a static website.
- **Vitepress** ([https://vitepress.vuejs.org/]({{$url0}})): A tool used alongside Obsidian to convert and share notes as a static website.
- **Notion** ([https://www.notion.so/]({{$url0}})): A collaborative workspace used for creating and sharing content, notable for its API which allows integration with other services.
- **Wooting 60HE** ([https://wooting.io/]({{$url0}})): A keyboard used for typing, featuring customizable settings like maximum key repeat rate and minimal delay until repeat.
- **Spotify** ([https://www.spotify.com/]({{$url0}})): A music streaming service used for listening to music while working.
- **Endel** ([https://endel.io/]({{$url0}})): An application used for generating focus-enhancing soundscapes.
- **Xnapper** ([https://xnapper.com/]({{$url0}})): A tool for taking screenshots during work processes.
- **ray.so** ([https://ray.so/]({{$url0}})): A service for generating code snippets, automated via Puppeteer macros.
- **TinyPNG** ([https://tinypng.com/]({{$url0}})): An image optimization tool used through automation macros.
- **Dropshare** ([https://dropshare.app/]({{$url0}})): A file-sharing application used for sharing images and files.
- **DigitalOcean** ([https://www.digitalocean.com/]({{$url0}})): A hosting service used for storing images and files.
- **Paste** ([https://setapp.com/apps/paste]({{$url0}})): A clipboard manager that facilitates easier text editing and access to previously copied content.
- **Linear** ([https://linear.app/]({{$url0}})): A task management tool used for organizing work, favored for its API, clear GUI, and keyboard shortcuts.
- **Slack** ([https://slack.com/]({{$url0}})): A communication platform used for messaging the AI assistant and managing tasks.
- **Google Workspace** ([https://workspace.google.com/]({{$url0}})): A suite of productivity tools used for email management and automation.
- **Superhuman** ([https://superhuman.com/]({{$url0}})): An email client used alongside Gmail for enhanced email management and keyboard shortcuts.
- **make.com** ([https://make.com/]({{$url0}})): An automation platform used for setting up scenarios and integrating various tools.
- **Zencal** ([https://zencal.io/]({{$url0}})): A scheduling tool used for booking calendar slots, with automation capabilities.
- **Notion Calendar** ([https://www.notion.so/product/calendar]({{$url0}})): A calendar application within Notion, offering keyboard shortcuts and a minimalist interface.
- **Arc Browser** ([https://arc.net/]({{$url0}})): The primary web browser used for internet browsing, featuring a Command Bar and Little Arc for enhanced functionality.
- **Feedly** ([https://feedly.com/]({{$url0}})): A news aggregator used for staying updated on various topics, integrated with Make.com for automation.
- **Product Hunt** ([https://www.producthunt.com/]({{$url0}})): A platform used for discovering new products and trends.
- **daily.dev** ([https://app.daily.dev/onboarding]({{$url0}})): A site used for aggregating developer-focused content and news.
- **Indie Hackers** ([https://www.indiehackers.com/]({{$url0}})): A community platform used for networking and finding inspiration among indie developers.
- **HackerNews** ([https://news.ycombinator.com/]({{$url0}})): A news aggregator focused on technology and startup news.
- **Algolia** ([https://www.algolia.com/]({{$url0}})): A search engine service used for linking with long-term memory in AI assistants.
- **Qdrant** ([https://qdrant.tech/]({{$url0}})): A vector search engine used for enhancing search capabilities within AI memory systems.
- **Figma** ([https://figma.com/]({{$url0}})): A graphic design tool used for UI and promotional material design, leveraging components and auto-layout features.

- **Adobe Photoshop Beta** ([https://www.adobe.com/products/photoshop.html]({{$url0}})): An image editing tool used for editing images and assets generated in Midjourney, enhanced with Generative AI features.
- **Midjourney** ([https://www.midjourney.com/]({{$url0}})): A Generative AI tool used for creating graphic and asset variants.
- **Adobe Firefly** ([https://www.adobe.com/products/firefly.html]({{$url0}})): A tool used alongside Photoshop for editing generated graphics.
- **Webflow** ([https://webflow.com/]({{$url0}})): A web design tool used in combination with HTMLCSSToImage for automatic graphic generation based on templates.
- **HTMLCSSToImage** ([https://htmlcsstoimage.com/]({{$url0}})): A service that converts HTML and CSS to images, used for automating graphic creation based on templates.

- **IntelliJ IDEA** ([https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/]({{$url0}})): The primary code editor used for programming in languages like TypeScript and Rust, favored for its customization and understanding of code.
- **Supermaven** ([https://supermaven.com/]({{$url0}})): An alternative to Github Copilot, offering intelligent code suggestions.
- **iTerm** ([https://iterm2.com/]({{$url0}})): A terminal emulator chosen for its simplicity and performance.
- **TablePlus** ([https://tableplus.com/]({{$url0}})): A database client used for managing databases on macOS.
- **Raycast** ([https://www.raycast.com/]({{$url0}})): An application used for searching and executing menu items, enhancing productivity with additional shortcuts.
- **Shortcuts** ([https://apps.apple.com/us/app/shortcuts/id915249334]({{$url0}})): An Apple application used for creating automation workflows.
- **Keyboard Maestro** ([https://folivora.ai/]({{$url0}})): A macOS tool used for creating keyboard shortcuts and automations.
- **Better Touch Tool** ([https://folivora.ai/]({{$url0}})): A tool used for customizing trackpad gestures and touch inputs.
- **Goodreads** ([https://www.goodreads.com/]({{$url0}})): A platform used for logging and sharing book titles and notes.
- **Amazon Kindle** ([https://play.google.com/store/apps/details]({{$url0}})): An app used for reading e-books.
- **Audible** ([https://www.audible.com/]({{$url0}})): An audiobook service used for listening to books.
- **PlayStation 5** ([https://www.playstation.com/en-us/ps5/]({{$url0}})): A gaming console used for playing games.
- **Nvidia GeForce Now** ([https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/geforce-now/]({{$url0}})): A game streaming service used for accessing Steam games remotely.
- **Steam Deck** ([https://www.steampowered.com/steamdeck]({{$url0}})): A handheld gaming device used for playing Steam games on the go.
- **Nintendo Switch** ([https://www.nintendo.com/switch/]({{$url0}})): A versatile gaming console used for both handheld and TV gaming.
- **endel.io** ([https://endel.io/]({{$url0}})): An application used for generating focus-enhancing soundscapes while working.
- **heyalice.app** ([https://heyalice.app/]({{$url0}})): A platform related to AI assistants, differentiated from the personal AI assistant described.
